<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-01-19T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-01-19T22:00:00-05:00" n="844" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d844">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1111 Nelson, Bert N./56:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-01-20T11:00:00+08:00">January 20, 1931—11
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received January 20—6 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>32. Legation’s 5, January 6, noon.<note n="5" xml:id="d844fn5">Not
                                printed.</note> Following from American Consul at Hankow: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“January 19, 4 p.m. Nelson<note n="6" xml:id="d844fn6">Rev. Bert
                                        N. Nelson, American missionary kidnaped on October 5,
                                        1930.</note> has been taken by his captors across the Hupeh
                                    border into Anhwei. I have notified military authorities and
                                    again urged that some definite and sustained effort be made to
                                    effect release. I suggest that the case be brought once more to
                                    attention of Nanking authorities.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <p>Repeated to Nanking.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>